# Exodus CI/CD Engine

## Core Principle: Databricks-Native

All CI/CD compute runs on **Databricks job compute** — auto-provisions, auto-terminates.
Never use SQL Warehouses for CI/CD (wrong compute model, too expensive).

## Per-PR Schema Lifecycle

### dbt Core clients
```
PR opened
  → CREATE SCHEMA {client}_ci.pr_{number}
  → shallow clone prod tables (baseline)
  → ironlayer plan (validate execution, cost estimate)
  → dbt build --target ci --select {changed_models}+
  → data diff (ci vs prod: row counts, distributions, nulls)
  → anomaly detection (statistical outliers)
  → lineage query (downstream impact)
  → post structured PR comment

PR merged/closed
  → DROP SCHEMA {client}_ci.pr_{number} CASCADE
```

### SQLMesh clients (Virtual Data Environments — free, no schema cloning cost)
```
PR opened
  → ironlayer plan --framework sqlmesh (validate, cost estimate)
  → sqlmesh plan ci_pr_{number} --no-prompts (Virtual Data Environment)
  → sqlmesh run --environment ci_pr_{number}
  → sqlmesh test (unit tests)
  → sqlmesh table_diff prod:ci_pr_{number} {changed_model}
  → post structured PR comment (plan summary + table diff)

PR merged/closed
  → sqlmesh plan prod --no-prompts (pointer swap — near-instant)
  → sqlmesh run --environment prod
  → Virtual Data Environment ci_pr_{number} auto-cleaned
```

**SQLMesh advantage:** Virtual Data Environments are view pointer swaps — no data copying, near-zero CI cost vs. Databricks ephemeral schema cloning for large tables.

## GitHub Actions Per-Repo CI Strategy

### exodus-core
```yaml
# .github/workflows/ci.yml
jobs:
  lint:     ruff check . + mypy .
  test:     uv run pytest tests/ -v --cov=exodus_core
  build:    python -m build (wheel)
  publish:  pypi publish (on tag)
```

### ironlayer_oss
```yaml
jobs:
  lint:     ruff + mypy
  test:     pytest
  docker:   Build + push to GHCR
  deploy:   Deploy MCP server (on main merge)
```

### ironlayer_infra
```yaml
jobs:
  terraform-validate:  terraform fmt -check + terraform validate
  dbt-compile:         dbt compile --target ci
  dbt-test:            dbt test --target ci (schema tests only — no data)
  terraform-plan:      terraform plan (PR comment with plan output)
```

### exodus-autopilot
```yaml
jobs:
  lint:          ruff + mypy
  test:          pytest tests/unit/ -v
  docker:        Build + push to GHCR
  deploy-ec2:    Deploy webhook to EC2 (on main merge)
  deploy-mac:    Deploy Ollama models + Docker to Mac Studio (on tag)
```

### exodus-terraform
```yaml
jobs:
  fmt-check:   terraform fmt -check -recursive
  validate:    terraform validate
  plan:        terraform plan (post as PR comment)
  apply:       terraform apply (on main merge, after human approval)
```

### Data-eXchange
```yaml
jobs:
  fmt:     cargo fmt --check
  clippy:  cargo clippy -- -D warnings
  test:    cargo test
  build:   cargo build --release (artifacts)
```

## GitHub Actions Runners

- **ubuntu-latest** — Default for lint, type-check, unit tests, Docker builds
- **mac-studio** (self-hosted, M4 Max) — Ollama model tests, heavy integration tests, Docker builds with ARM images

```yaml
jobs:
  test-local-llm:
    runs-on: [self-hosted, mac-studio]
    steps:
      - name: Test Ollama health
        run: curl -s http://localhost:11434/api/tags
```

## Data Diff SQL Patterns

```sql
-- Row count comparison
SELECT 'prod' AS env, COUNT(*) AS row_count FROM {prod_catalog}.gold.{table}
UNION ALL
SELECT 'ci'   AS env, COUNT(*) AS row_count FROM {ci_catalog}.pr_{number}.{table};

-- Metric distribution (numeric columns)
SELECT
    '{col}'                                                    AS column_name,
    ROUND(AVG({col}), 4)                                       AS mean,
    ROUND(STDDEV({col}), 4)                                    AS stddev,
    MIN({col})                                                 AS min_val,
    MAX({col})                                                 AS max_val,
    ROUND(PERCENTILE_CONT(0.5) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY {col}), 4) AS median
FROM {ci_catalog}.pr_{number}.{table};
```

## Lineage Queries (Unity Catalog)

```sql
-- Downstream tables impacted by a changed table
SELECT target_table_full_name, target_type, entity_type
FROM system.access.table_lineage
WHERE source_table_full_name = '{catalog}.{schema}.{table}'
  AND event_time > current_timestamp() - INTERVAL 30 DAYS;
```

## IronLayer Plan Gate

Before every `dbt build` or `sqlmesh run` in CI, IronLayer validates the execution plan:

```bash
# dbt projects
ironlayer plan \
  --manifest target/manifest.json \
  --target ci \
  --require-confidence 70 \
  --block-on-findings BLOCK

# SQLMesh projects (auto-detected)
ironlayer plan \
  --framework sqlmesh \
  --require-confidence 70 \
  --block-on-findings BLOCK
```

CI fails if:
- `confidence < 70`
- Any BLOCK-severity finding
- Cost estimate > `$CI_COST_LIMIT` (default $2)

