## Cursor CLI in CI

[Cursor CLI](https://cursor.com/cli) enables headless agent runs from GitHub Actions and terminal scripts.
Use it for agent-driven tasks that go beyond simple linting: generating PR summaries, auto-fixing WARN findings,
or running a planning pass on a complex diff.

```yaml
# .github/workflows/cursor-agent.yml
- name: Install Cursor CLI
  run: curl -fsSL https://cursor.com/install.sh | sh

- name: Run Cursor agent on PR diff
  env:
    CURSOR_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.CURSOR_API_KEY }}
  run: |
    cursor agent \
      --prompt "Review the diff in this PR for BLOCK/WARN/NOTE findings using exodus review standards" \
      --model auto \
      --output review-output.md

- name: Post review as PR comment
  uses: actions/github-script@v7
  with:
    script: |
      const fs = require('fs');
      const body = fs.readFileSync('review-output.md', 'utf8');
      github.rest.issues.createComment({ issue_number: context.issue.number, body });
```

**When to use Cursor CLI in CI:**
- Auto-generate PR descriptions from diff (`cursor agent --prompt "Summarize this diff"`)
- Run a planning pass before complex migrations
- Generate dbt model documentation from source YAML
- Headless agent tasks on a schedule (cron workflows)

**When NOT to use:**
- Simple linting (use ruff/sqlfluff directly — cheaper)
- Tests (use pytest directly)
- Standard CI checks (use existing jobs)

