## Bugbot Integration

[Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/bugbot) is a free automated pre-merge code review that runs on every PR.
Enable it on all ironlayer org repos as a **complement** to the custom Exodus review engine (not a replacement).

**Setup:**
1. Install the Cursor Bugbot GitHub App on the `ironlayer` org
2. Add `.cursor/bugbot.json` to each repo:

```json
{
  "enabled": true,
  "severity_threshold": "warn",
  "auto_fix": false,
  "ignore_patterns": [
    "**/__pycache__/**",
    "**/.venv/**",
    "uv.lock",
    "**/*.lock"
  ]
}
```

3. Configure as a required check in branch protection rules

**Bugbot vs. Exodus Review Engine:**

| Capability | Bugbot | Exodus Review Engine |
|------------|--------|---------------------|
| General code bugs | ✅ | ✅ |
| dbt/SQL conventions | ❌ | ✅ |
| Data diff | ❌ | ✅ |
| Client-specific rules | ❌ | ✅ |
| Schema drift | ❌ | ✅ |
| Cost | Free | Credits |

Run Bugbot first (free), then Exodus engine only if Bugbot passes. This conserves AI credits.

