## Cloud Agents API

The [Cloud Agents API](https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent/api/endpoints) enables programmatic agent launches
with webhooks and status polling. Use this to automate the PR review + healing loop without manual `@cursor` invocations.

```bash
# Launch a Cloud Agent via API
curl -X POST https://api.cursor.com/agents \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $CURSOR_API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "prompt": "Review PR #42 in ironlayer/ironlayer_infra for BLOCK findings",
    "model": "auto",
    "repo": "ironlayer/ironlayer_infra",
    "branch": "feature/new-dbt-models"
  }'

# Poll for completion
curl https://api.cursor.com/agents/{agent_id}/status \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $CURSOR_API_KEY"
```

**Integration with EC2 webhook router:**
The EC2 instance receives GitHub webhooks → dispatches Cloud Agent runs via API → posts results back to PR.
This replaces the need for `@cursor` comments on every PR.

```python
# exodus-autopilot/webhook.py pattern
@app.post("/github/webhook")
async def handle_pr(payload: dict):
    if payload["action"] == "opened":
        agent_id = await launch_cloud_agent(
            prompt=f"Review PR #{payload['number']} ...",
            repo=payload["repository"]["full_name"],
        )
        await store_agent_job(pr_number=payload["number"], agent_id=agent_id)
    return {"status": "queued"}
```

