## Parallel Agents / Worktrees

[Cursor Worktrees](https://cursor.com/docs/configuration/worktrees) enable multiple agents to work on
different branches simultaneously, each in an isolated git worktree with its own environment.

**Configuration (already set up at `.cursor/worktrees.json`):**
```json
{
  "setup-worktree-unix": [
    "uv sync --frozen 2>/dev/null || uv sync",
    "cp $ROOT_WORKTREE_PATH/.env .env 2>/dev/null || true"
  ]
}
```

**Use cases:**
- **Best-of-N review:** Launch 2 agents on the same PR diff with different prompts, pick the better review
- **Parallel feature development:** Agent A works on the Python extractor, Agent B works on dbt models simultaneously
- **Regression comparison:** One agent on `main`, one on `feature/` — compare outputs

**Worktree lifecycle:**
```bash
# Cursor manages this automatically, but you can also use git manually:
git worktree add ../ironlayer_infra-pr-42 feature/pr-42-models
cd ../ironlayer_infra-pr-42
uv sync --frozen
# Agent runs here in isolation
git worktree remove ../ironlayer_infra-pr-42
```
